caption: This place provides excellent service and delicious menu. One of the best place around town. The food and drinks arrived fast and the rates were reasonable. I recommend this place.
Bland food and horrible service!
Favorite Thai place ever! I have never ordered anything at this restaurant that hasn't been delicious. The Pad Se Ew is divine! Best I have ever had. Order from them, you will NOT be disappointed.
My go-to takeout place. Best pad see ew and chive dumplings ever 👌

This site is my favorite restaurant.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to that place. Whenever  I feel like having a special lunch, this is the place that comes immediately to my head.  Great and many types of  food and a rich cuisine.helpful staff members, and great atmosphere. Not less important, the bill is affordable. I recommend this restaurant with pleasure.
Superb atmosphere and very amiable service. The food was crisp and enchanting. Will clearly recommend this restaurant to friends. Affordable prices and large meals. Good job.

The Drunken Noodles with beef is so good.  Some might say it's on the salty side but if you're ordering Drunken Noodles, I'm guessing you're up for savory.  The portions are very generous, enough for 2.  Lots of meat.  I ordered it once with seafood and in comparison, it was light on the seafood.  The Pad See Ew and Sweet Basil are also good.

If your go to Thai dish is drunken noodles then this place hits out our perfectly!! It’s been closed so far during Covid pandemic and I’m waiting patiently for them to reopen!! I always get drunken noodles with beef and it’s always good. Hopefully it will open soon.

Opai Thai is my equivalent to Cheers! It's a spot where everybody knows my name and my order! Since locating this gem during my grad school days, they have yet to disappoint.  I literally drool thinks about their drunken noodles and the consistency can't be beat. It's never crowded, but don't let that deter you. I'm sure folks are home ordering and watching Netflix while downing their basil fried rice!  Take yourself, take a friend, take a date, take your mom...you will love it and you will return! Great food, great service and a lovely intimate vibe.
I’ve been to Thailand and can honestly say the food here is very authentic. They will modify the spice upon request to suit your taste. The lunch specials are an incredible deal and not to be missed

I've been going here for years. This place makes some lovely drinks, the chicken pad thai is consistently good. Friends of mine have ordered other things like pad se ew, pineapple fried rice, tom yum soup - no complaints, they loved it. Every time I bring friends they fall in love and also become opai addicts. The service sometimes is slow and wonky (last I went they forgot to ask us if we wanted drinks- was remedied later on) however the staff here is always friendly, food is always made quickly. I love this place and it's one of my NY staples.
fresh and so tasty this is my first time getting food from here and will be returning! :)
Horrible customer service and extremely unprofessional, food was never even sent out. Very rude when asking what happened to the food.
The place is a joke as far as deliveries are concerned.  They missed the delivery window and then the restaurant closed!  How absurd.  Avoid at all costs.
This spot is one of my favorites! Good pricing, big portions and the employees are constantly very kind.
Amazing
Great service and delicious food!
Great food, my go to take out for Thai. Love the chicken satay and crab rangoon. Always fast and friendly delivery as well.
Yummy! The drinks could use some work.

We had a super-delicious meal, with fresh ingredients and delicious spices. My husband then forgot an important (to him) item at the restaurant, and the staff were extremely kind and mailed it to him. They really went beyond what can reasonably be expected in customer service! Thanks, Opai Thai!
Delicious food, large portions, wonderful service!

So fresh and delicious! I ordered drunken noodles and thai tea and they were delivered quickly. I received a huge portion of very fresh, delicious, and richly seasoned food for a very reasonable price. I love Thai food and live in the neighborhood so I will definitely be ordering more often. Couldn't be happier!

This restaurant, I will never order again! I had very bad experience with their food! I ordered sweet basil with beef along with some extra broccoli. Shockingly, the broccoli came out so moldy with a bad odor. I felt uneasy and made me sick in a matter of time. Healthy choice of food matters. I would not recommend to order anything from them anytime soon.
Awesome and yummy food, I love the ambience this spot has, and the cashiers were very nice. I will surely come back.
Worst curry dish I've ever had! Watered down, no taste! Potatoes were hard. Better off going anywhere but this place! I love thai and have it every week, and this place let me down.

I meet friends in this restaurant  a lot! This is my favorite restaurant to eat.  I go to this spot many times. The meals are just great, the workers are courteous and the prices are decent. I enjoy going in this spot over a tasty meal.

Passed by, with my phone in my pocket! Maybe I should try & give a real review! I do like Thai food, & it's probably GOOD! Nust have to check the prices first!

Unfortunately, this place has changed recently. They used to give the biggest portions of any Thai place in Manhattan. I was a regular, ordering the cashew nut and pad ped lunch specials and dinner servings, as the variety of vegetables and flavors were incredible, and the containers were filled to the top. Now the containers are barely filled halfway, and the variety of vegetables has been reduced, and more inedible items like peppercorns are placed into the portion. I've seen this before, this is what happens a few months before a place goes out of business. Well, they lost me as a customer.

Local food shopping area..!!!! Great variety of foods and vegetables.!!!!!!
The beef pad see ew Rocked! As did the curry puffs and the chicken, coconut milk soup. And the prices seemed reasonable. Over all very pleased with my takeout :)
This is a nice low key spot
They had pretty nice salads: grilled shrimp and avocado, my friend enjoyed their mojito. The atmosphere was mellow and relaxed.

This place reminds me of my favorite Thai places in the San Francisco bay area. Their lunch menu is super affordable at less than $10 for an entree and appetizer. The delivery takes a bit but my food was incredibly hot and very good. It's hard to find a Thai place that has good noodles. This place serves good broad thin noodles, and thin pad Thai noodles.
Came for some pad Thai
Would give this place 10 stars if I could. So good!
Delishish food yum yum great customer svc with reasonable pricing a tasty 💎...
Very good food
Great great great! ❤❤❤
Great tasty food. Great prices.

Opai Thai is my favorite restaurant in UWS, located at Amsterdam Av. Lunch special costs 9 dolars, apetizer and main course included. It is a comfortable place, delicious thai food. Close to the 96st st station, 1, 2 and 3 trains. No outside seats. Gender neutral restrooms.
Delicious food. Good price

High chairs available, kid friendly. Great every day lunch special. Great food. Great price.
We went here for lunch. They have really excellent versions of standard American Thai dishes at extremely affordable prices. The service was excellent and they were very accommodating of our toddler.
Very happy place , charming,  decorations are very nice, staff ,employess,top of the line What experience .you defenilly want to back again
The food is delicious

My go to Thai place. Sad that since we moved neighborhoods, we won’t have  access to it. My go to ritual with my boyfriend is that when we are having a night in, we pick a show and order opal thai’s Tom yum rice, dumplings, and Thai iced tea. Went to the actual resto once but it just tastes so much better as takeout eaten in your pjs. We will miss you so much Opai Thai!

Conveniently located Thai joint in a spot with a good collection of interesting eating places bunched together over 2 or 3 blocks on Amsterdam Ave. Good food, good drinks and good service at regular prices. This is one of the few Thai places that uses Green peppercorns (or knows about them), which is a good sign of Thai food authenticity :-).
Great service
Food was really tasty. Service was timely. Establishment was clean. Also, was not crowded on a Sunday afternoon.
Never been
Good food, I went out with a friend to grab some lunch and I ordered a pineapple fried rice with beef.  To my surprise they take the pineapple part seriously.  I give them an A+ for presentation.
Best pad see ew in the city. Huge portions. Don’t bother with the Pad thai.
To-go portions are huge and delicious!
Great Thai
I had the pineapple rice chicken meal, and it was tasteless.
Tried for first time Sat June 8th had searched for a new Thai restaurant as last favorite closed. Opai is a great find, fabulous Massaman, generous servings.... A must try!
Poor quality and tasteless food (home delivered)

Horrible food and service. Absolutely disgusting fried rice - drenched in oil, salty, no flavor with uncooked meat. Check out all other 1 star reviews here, they are very accurate. They know nothing of Thai spices and simply very rude. I ordered from here today and they arrived after 1.5 hrs when they estimated 30-40 mins. No apologies, the first person who picked up the phone hung up on me when I asked for a refund. When I called again they said they'd arrive in 3 mins, it took another 10. The food delivered was drenched in oil (when I had specifically asked for less oil), no flavor whatsoever but salty, bits of burnt flakes I couldn't identify and some of the beef was pink so I threw it out. When I called again to really ask for a refund, they simply stopped picking up the phone. Seamless reimbursed me, but the restaurant apparently said that I wanted the food (I did, until I had to wait even longer and see the horrible food) and refused to reimburse. You have some balls to operate like this when people can freely exchange their experiences and honest opinions online. My full name is listed and I can't remember ever writing anything on yelp but here it is. The worst food and service I've ever had NYC since my residence starting 2008, the only time I have ever had to call the Seamless customer service for my money back. If you think this food is edible you have absolutely no taste. If the Tom Yum fried rice tastes like burnt meat (it is supposed to be the most flavorful, but had no trace of lemongrassy spices in it - just salty and disgustingly oily) I can only guess what other orders must taste like. I asked for "thai spicy" in the order, too. Not spicy at all of course. This places knows nothing of thai spices and the kitchen is insanitary. The burnt pieces and pink meat were disgusting. I couldn't touch the food even after starving all day. Check out your latest ratings on seamless. People are picking up on the horrible service and food, and your business won't survive much longer like this. Why put garbage down my throat when there are tones of good options in UWS. I hope more people realize this sooner and do not waste their time and money. Big portions of garbage, served by people with no morals. Good luck.

This is my favorite spot in the UWS for Thai! Definitely check them out! The prices are extremely fair and the portion sizes are giant (with lots of meat in the meat dishes)! Great deal!  I have been here and ordered from here many times and after taking a break from this restaurant when their quality seemed to be going down, they have clearly made changes, and I have found the food to be better, fresher, and more flavorfully spiced than ever!  I got a yellow curry with chicken and it was probably the best meal of that dish I have ever eaten! Their Thai iced tea is also AMAZING! My friend got the pineapple fried rice which was also very good. We split spring rolls and they were tasty and fresh and delicious too.  This time I dined at the restaurant. Whenever I order they are always speedy with delivery as well! They do a lot of pickups and deliveries so they are pretty fast. I like to order in when I'm feeling lazy but like most restaurants their serving dishes are different from their takeout dishes and I think you get a bit more food when you go into the restaurant (portions are still large for takeout just making an observation).
Delicious flavor... I ordered the Tom Yum soup and Pad Thai for takeout. The portion was also enormous! Has enough for leftovers twice! Great value
Every time I come here , food is delicious and at fair price
Always great food and delivery always fast. Not one bad word to say about this place!
Best thai food portions in the UWS/Harlem area!
4 of us agreed....One of the best time meals we've had
Overpriced for decent food. What we got was super salty. But the ice coffee is bomb

Order with seamless. discover there is lunch special. didn't let me change my order. and didn't let me cancel my order or refund before i even got it I used to order from them once a week. not anymore
My massaman curry was more like a massaman soup and wasn’t very flavorful. Disappointing. Tum & Yum a few blocks away is a much better option.
Nice cool spot to eat and have drinks. I usually go there for apple rice and with shrimps, the food is very good!

I used to like this place. I liked their Drunken Noodle and the lunch prices were great. But today they messed up my order. I know that happens everywhere in the world but I asked for vegetable Pad Thai but they gave me Pad Thai with beef and shrimp. I can't eat beef. When I called the woman apologized that she mixed it up with the vegetable pad thai and kept asking over and over if it was okay even though I told her I'm not allowed to eat beef. Very dismissive and mainly just wanted me to be okay so she wouldn't get in trouble. No, it's not okay. People can't eat certain foods because of allergies, religious, or health reasons. You need to be more mindful or at least step up when you mess up. Never ordering here again.

Not usually crowded on weeknights.. chicken pad Thai is average, but the Forest Curry is fantastic - chock full of unique veggies like Thai Aubergine (eggplant), doesn’t have coconut milk which is a unique change of pace, and you can order it mild so it’s not as spicy - which turned out to be perfect for someone who does like spicy food even.
Overall is a good place to eat, I feel last time I order it was very little for a pad thai.
Large portion of vegetable pad Thai. Definitely a unique pad Thai experience good bang for your buck. Next time I’ll try something else from their menu

Extremely dissatisfied- ordered veggie pad Thai to go. Food was put in plastic containers at an insanely hot temperature (probably unsafe).  Food continued to cook itself inside - noodles were fused together into almost a paste, the few veggies in there were cooked to death and mushy, almost no tofu in there.  Portion of noodles was absurd and the tomato base sauce was just nasty. Never again will I eat from here.

This place is disgusting my food delivery came late and cold and the shrimp pad thai smelled horrible the shrimp itself tastes bad i had to throw it away and when i called to complain the staff was very rude and unfriendly id never recomend it to anyone, 0 stars and a big thumbs down dont ever eat here!!!

I ordered the lunch special Pad Thai and Sweet and Sour (with Shrimp). I eat Thai food on a daily basis... I'm obsessed. I have my favorite spots however, the one I typically go to was closed so I decided to try a new place. Unfortunately I am regretting this decision. I literally just threw away all of the food. The Pad Thai had a pungent smell that made me question if I should even try it. The taste was worse... bitter and unpleasant. The Sweet and Sour platter lacked flavor (despite being drowned in sauce). The shrimp were mushy and taste "fishy" which indicated they were no good. I will NEVER eat from here again. The food lacks authenticity and is poorly made.
You can get much better Thai in the area. Unremarkable.

Ordered curry Thai standard.  Asked them to make it spicy.  Told them I wouldn't return it.  My curry was devoid of spice.  0/5.  Don't go here if you care about spice in your curry.  I would give this place a zero out of five if I could.
Very Good Thai Food for a good value! (currently 10$ for a veggie/tofu main course). The atmosphere wasn't bustling as much, so good for a quieter night.
The worst "thai" food ever! Very lazy and poor food, made of ketchup to add flavor.
Drunken Noodle is delicious. No outdoor seating, though.

I ordered pipeapple fried rice. Drunken noodle. Classic fried rice and pad thai. Despite good location and friendly waitress, The food is average, salty and lean toward the mushy side. I never drink 2 cup of water in US before but here.
Great tasting, good quality Thai food! I am a food Thai food snob and this place is always 👌🏾👌🏾👌🏾
Omg I think this is the best Thai I have ever eaten 😍😍😍 I think I found a new spot

Great Thai food, one of the best on the Upper West. Their green curry fried rice, Tom Yum fried rice, and Drunken Noodles are the best. They have a full bar too, and is one of those places where you'll feel totally welcome, relaxed and comfortable eating alone too.
I love this place absolutely love it a hundred and 110% especially the crab rangoons their small bite-size but it's just the perfect bite.
Great food, decent prices
The food is of good quality. The service is very good, and the prices are reasonable.

We started with a fried tofu and dipping sauce appetiser for two. It tasted freshly prepared and not overdone. The Pad Thai and Pad See Ew were both generous portions and arrived hot and flavorful. An error on our bill was dealt with quickly and professionally. Will go back to try other dishes.
This place is the best. Best Asian food. Great customer service. And a beautiful place, you also feel your self welcome and is a relaxing place. I love this places.
I love their Crab Rangoon Wontons, I also usually get their Pad Se Ew with chicken and vegetables, it's really delicious and satisfying.
Great customer service and everyone must try their Pad See Uew
Based on delivery experience only. On time, great flavor (and spicy actually is spicy!), nice portions. Will order again.
A good neighborhood Thai place, where I've been many time. Service always good, if not polished, and food a step above other local Thai's I've tried.
Good food, always deliver quickly, great lunch specials. Favorite dishes are the pad see ew and the massaman curry.
Big fan of the Pad See Yew here! I've never had a problem with delivery.
The worst food I have ever eaten , plus the food was cold when served

I will never go to this restaurant again.  The place has new owners and the new chef is not very good. I ordered the lemongrass pork chops and was very disappointed. The chops are suppose to be crispy with lots of flavor. Even though I asked for well done, they arrived very pale with the fat on the edges pretty raw. In addition to the food just being so-so, the servers are cold and not friendly. I miss the old owners.
Really like the drunken noodles here!

Great place to eat Thai Food! I go here all the time and am never disappointed with my order.

They used to be good.  But you can't rely on them.  The food arrives cold, over 3o minutes past their promised delivery time.  And they hang up on you when you call to try to get information on your order.
Amazing Thai food for good prices and open late!! I go here when I want bomb Thai.

I tried a lot of thai foods at a lot of thai restaurants. And I can say that this restaurant is one of the best. And service was good too.
one of the best restaurant in this region. especially, the beef noodle is really nice!!

Opai has probably the best Thai food within its 4-block radius. Food is solid & consistent - though I have a slight preference of their noodle dishes (e.g. drunken noodles, pad see ew) versus fried rice dishes. Can't beat the $8 lunch pre-fix! I also like their thai ice tea.  Staff is super friendly. They always pour me water while I wait for take out - such a nice gesture :)  Will return very soon to try their other dishes!

My go to Thai restaurant in the UWS. I know there are other options, but this one is nearby and offers great meals. I usually stick to the noodles but some of their rice dishes are great. Massamman curry her is amazing.  Stop by during lunch for their deal and get a free thai iced tea as well!  The service is awesome and the waiters are super nice. I've never had to wait to be seated either.
Very clean place but food didnot have enough flavor!:(
